{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-blog-post-js","path":"/projects/poetry/","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 590px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/52f6f096dbbd5079e044ee572e7cb623/a8c87/poetry.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 98.64864864864865%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Conceptulilization process\"\n        title=\"Conceptulilization process\"\n        src=\"/static/52f6f096dbbd5079e044ee572e7cb623/fcda8/poetry.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/52f6f096dbbd5079e044ee572e7cb623/12f09/poetry.png 148w,\n/static/52f6f096dbbd5079e044ee572e7cb623/e4a3f/poetry.png 295w,\n/static/52f6f096dbbd5079e044ee572e7cb623/fcda8/poetry.png 590w,\n/static/52f6f096dbbd5079e044ee572e7cb623/efc66/poetry.png 885w,\n/static/52f6f096dbbd5079e044ee572e7cb623/c83ae/poetry.png 1180w,\n/static/52f6f096dbbd5079e044ee572e7cb623/a8c87/poetry.png 1538w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Looks neat!</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p><em>- Ziba, creator of Kind Words (lofi chill beats to write to)</em></p>\n<h1>The Game</h1>\n<p>Poetry is a 3D point and click game set in the gallery of the mind. The player uses paintings hung on the wall to create poems.\nIt was made for the 2021 Global Game Jam.</p>\n<h1>The Team</h1>\n<p>Poetry was made primarily by myself and Jamie Camera. </p>\n<p>A theme of the project was collaboration, so we had additional help from many artists who contributed to the first collage. </p>\n<h1>My Role</h1>\n<p>My roles included:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Gallery Artist (using Pro Builder and Substance Designer)</li>\n<li>Poem System Programmer</li>\n<li>Poem Writer</li>\n<li>UI Designer</li>\n</ul>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 590px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/ccac50aa311ac8df62fa5cc49481eb80/7de01/3Qt%2B6B.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 73.64864864864865%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Poetry Room\"\n        title=\"Poetry Room\"\n        src=\"/static/ccac50aa311ac8df62fa5cc49481eb80/fcda8/3Qt%2B6B.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/ccac50aa311ac8df62fa5cc49481eb80/12f09/3Qt%2B6B.png 148w,\n/static/ccac50aa311ac8df62fa5cc49481eb80/e4a3f/3Qt%2B6B.png 295w,\n/static/ccac50aa311ac8df62fa5cc49481eb80/fcda8/3Qt%2B6B.png 590w,\n/static/ccac50aa311ac8df62fa5cc49481eb80/7de01/3Qt%2B6B.png 794w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<h1>Process</h1>\n<p>We started the 48 hours putting together the \"mind gallery.\" A minimalistic yet ornate space where memories are exhibted. This let me play around with materials and lighting, which was a grand old time to be honest.</p>\n<p>The second half the jam was focused on getting the game system working. My focus was on the Poem.cs class. This class managed the creation of poems and the UI associated with them. </p>\n<pre><code class=\"language-c#\">public void HoverLine(string word)                                     \n    {                                                                   \n        switch (thisPoem)                                               \n        {                                                               \n            case PoemType.Adlib:                                        \n                textChange(Lines[lineIndex].Replace(\"___\", word));      \n                break;                                                  \n            case PoemType.LineByLine:                                   \n                textChange(GetLine(word));                              \n                break;                                                  \n        }                                                               \n    }                                                                   \n                                                                        \nprivate void textChange(string textC)                                   \n    {                                                                   \n        Sequence textSequence = DOTween.Sequence();                     \n        textSequence.Append(DOTweenModuleUI.DOFade(line_text, 0, .4f))  \n            .Append(DOTweenModuleUI.DOText(line_text,textC,0))          \n            .Append(DOTweenModuleUI.DOFade(line_text, 1, .4f));         \n    }                                                                  \n</code></pre>\n<h1>What I Learned</h1>","frontmatter":{"title":"Poetry","tags":["Unity","Photoshop","Substance Designer","ProBuilder"],"description":"","techs":["3d Artist","Designer","Programmer"],"v_link":"o71MknvPD_g","repo_link":null,"demo_link":"https://elijahcobb.itch.io/poetry","ios_link":null,"android_link":null,"date":"23. January 2020","cover_image":{"childImageSharp":{"fluid":{"